-- Barclays Sees Two More Years of Losses in Spain, Expansion Says
-- B y   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 2012-03-10T12:59:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-10/barclays-sees-two-more-years-of-losses-in-spain-expansion-says.html
The Spanish unit of  Barclays Plc (BARC) 
won’t become profitable until 2014 as it carries out
restructuring,  Expansion  reported, citing the bank’s 2011 annual
report.  The bank predicts that the country’s economic outlook will
remain challenging, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
